---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import Button from '../../components/Button.astro';

const retrospective = '/insights/we-pointed-muttr-at-our-own-site/';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="We Audited Our Own Site"
  description="We ran Muttr on weknowthewhy.com twice — what it caught, what we fixed, what we threw out, and how we used the results to make the tool better. Full transparency, receipts in the repo."
>
  <Section band="deep" class="pt-24 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-4">Proof &rsaquo; Self-Audit</p>
      <h1 class="mb-6">We audited our own site &mdash; twice.</h1>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-xl leading-relaxed mb-6">
        We run Muttr, Canary, and Delphi against weknowthewhy.com with the same
        standards we apply to client sites. Here's what they found, what we fixed,
        and what we threw out.
      </p>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-sm">
        Last updated: <span class="text-primary-text">July 6, 2026</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Muttr Results -->
  <Section elevated>
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="mb-6">Platform Technical Audit (Muttr)</h2>
      <div class="plate p-8 space-y-6 text-secondary-text leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          We ran Muttr against this site, remediated, and ran it again. The honest
          scorecard:
        </p>

        <div>
          <p class="text-primary-text font-medium mb-2">What it caught that was worth fixing.</p>
          <p>
            The first pass flagged ~80 issues; about a dozen were real &mdash;
            visitor IPs reaching Google's font CDN before consent (a GDPR exposure),
            tag manager loading before the consent banner could be answered, no
            security headers or Content Security Policy, and a dozen accessibility
            defects. All fixed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-primary-text font-medium mb-2">What we threw out &mdash; which matters just as much.</p>
          <p>
            The rest were stale, false, or passing checks dressed up as problems. It
            reported a 2.56&nbsp;MB app bundle from &ldquo;cart, checkout, and product
            configurators&rdquo; &mdash; we have none of those; our entire JavaScript
            is one 28&nbsp;KB component. We deleted it. It proposed a three-tier
            pricing grid; we sell one engagement, so we deleted that too.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-primary-text font-medium mb-2">Then we fixed the tool and re-ran it.</p>
          <p>
            Every ungrounded finding went back into Muttr as a fix. The second audit
            proved it: the phantom bundle was gone, the report was shorter and
            cleaner, and the real fixes held. It surfaced one new false positive
            &mdash; our working cookie banner, measured hidden instead of rendered
            &mdash; which we traced to root cause and filed the same day.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-primary-text">
          The failure modes we find, we train out. By the time these tools run on
          your site, the specific mistakes in our own audit have already been
          grounded out of them.
        </p>

        <div class="pt-2">
          <a href={retrospective} class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-medium underline">
            Read the full retrospective &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Canary Results -->
  <Section>
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="mb-6">Content Authority Audit (Canary)</h2>
      <div class="plate p-8 text-secondary-text leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          The same method, applied to content. We run Canary against our own topic
          coverage as the insights library grows &mdash; the summary lands here once
          there's enough published to audit honestly. We don't post a score we
          haven't earned.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Delphi Results -->
  <Section elevated>
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="mb-6">Revenue Performance Audit (Delphi)</h2>
      <div class="plate p-8 text-secondary-text leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          The same method, applied to measurement. Delphi verifies our analytics
          implementation once conversion tracking is fully established &mdash;
          results here when they're real and attributable, not before.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section band="deep">
    <div class="text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-4">Want to see what we'd find on yours?</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg mb-8">
        We apply the same rigor to every site we audit. Talk to a founder about
        what we'd find on yours.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <Button href="/contact">Talk to a Founder</Button>
        <Button href="/the-get-right" variant="secondary">Learn About The Get Right</Button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Structured Data: the self-audit results page as a WebPage tied to the
       sitewide Organization. Describes the three audits we run on ourselves;
       no Rating/Review nodes until real, attributable results are published (WL-17). -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebPage",
    "@id": "https://weknowthewhy.com/proof/our-site",
    "url": "https://weknowthewhy.com/proof/our-site",
    "name": "We Audited Our Own Site",
    "description": "We ran Muttr on weknowthewhy.com twice — what it caught, what we fixed, what we threw out, and how we used the results to make the tool better.",
    "about": { "@id": "https://weknowthewhy.com/#organization" },
    "publisher": { "@id": "https://weknowthewhy.com/#organization" },
    "isPartOf": { "@id": "https://weknowthewhy.com/proof" },
    "significantLink": [
      "https://weknowthewhy.com/insights/we-pointed-muttr-at-our-own-site",
      "https://weknowthewhy.com/the-get-right/platform",
      "https://weknowthewhy.com/the-get-right/content",
      "https://weknowthewhy.com/the-get-right/revenue",
    ],
  })} />
</BaseLayout>
